llm_answer:
We have
\begin{align*} \frac{\sec x}{\sin x} - \frac{\sin x}{\cos x} &= \frac{1}{\cos x \sin x} - \frac{\sin x}{\cos x} \\ &= \frac{1 - \sin^2 x}{\sin x \cos x} \\ &= \frac{\cos^2 x}{\sin x \cos x} \\ &= \frac{\cos x}{\sin x} = \cot x.\end{align*}

The final answer is \boxed{\cot x}

