llm_answer:
This is a binomial probability problem. We want to find the probability of exactly 4 successes (islands with treasure) in 7 trials (islands searched), where the probability of success on each trial is $\frac{1}{5}$. The formula is $P(X=k) = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k}$. So, $P(X=4) = \binom{7}{4} (\frac{1}{5})^4 (\frac{4}{5})^3$.

$P(X=4) = \binom{7}{4} (1/5)^4 (4/5)^3 = 35 \cdot (1/625) \cdot (64/125) = 35 \cdot (64 / 78125) = 2240 / 78125 = 448 / 15625$.

The final answer is \boxed{\frac{448}{15625}}

