Let $\mathbf{v}_1 = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -6 \end{pmatrix}$ be the direction vector of the first line, and $\mathbf{v}_2 = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -12 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix}$ be the direction vector of the second line. Then
\[ \cos \theta = \frac{\mathbf{v}_1 \cdot \mathbf{v}_2}{\|\mathbf{v}_1\| \|\mathbf{v}_2\|} = \frac{6 - 24 + 18}{\sqrt{9+4+36} \sqrt{4+144+9}} = \frac{0}{\sqrt{49} \sqrt{157}} = 0. \]Thus $\theta = 90^\circ.$

